<FindBugsFilter xmlns="https://github.com/spotbugs/filter/3.0.0">
  <!--
    No suppressions (Chapter 16: suppress with a reason, never disable a whole detector).

    This module's deliberate counter-examples are METRIC smells, not bytecode bugs: a deeply-nested
    method (DiscountRulesNested) and an over-fragmented one (DiscountRulesFragmented) are shapes Sonar
    java:S3776 (cognitive complexity) and PMD measure, while SpotBugs is a bytecode bug-finder that does
    not score complexity. All three forms compute the same correct result, so every class stays clean
    under SpotBugs at this module's threshold and the filter is empty by design. The detectors are left
    fully enabled; the cognitive cost of the nested form is shown by its score and the behaviour-
    preservation test, not held quiet by a suppression. Different tools see different smells — the
    chapter's point, shown rather than asserted (the same boundary the Chapter 19 module draws from the
    other side, where a real bytecode bug IS flagged).
  -->
</FindBugsFilter>
